The United Nations General Assembly voted to remove Russia from the UN Human Rights Council, with the United States leading efforts to drive this decision. The international community sees this as a significant step, reflecting Russia's status as an international pariah due to its gross violations of human rights and war crimes. As a result of the vote, Russia will no longer be able to participate in the Council's work or spread disinformation while an investigation into its human rights abuses in Ukraine takes place. The disturbing images emerging from Ukraine, including reports of rape, torture, and desecration of bodies, further reinforce the condemnation of Russia's aggression. The United States and other responsible nations will continue to gather evidence, hold Russia accountable for its atrocities, increase economic pressure, and isolate Russia on the global stage.